title: Our Values
text: We believe: Partying is an invaluable means of self-expression, community-building, and dignity-nurturing. It should be liberating, and in spaces where guests’ health and safety are the top-priority. Supporting partygoers’ health and well-being is an honor and a privilege Everyone deserves a safer space to gather and celebrate. The partygoer is the ultimate authority on their own safety and well-being. We, as health educators, must provide valuable information for self-care and wellbeing that honors autonomy and centers cultural respect.
